🍼🍼#18weeks Workout 🍼🍼 🤰💪🏽 getting it in!!!
Currently for my workouts, I’ve taken out my HIIT training and replaced it with some steady state cardio & short burst training like the battle ropes (monitoring my HR). I’ve removed my typical abs work and replaced it with pelvic floor work throughout the workout.
I still enjoy going in on the weights, but I pay attention to my breathing and I don’t do max weights so I can focus on my core engagement (not pushing my abs out at any point). I get about 3 workouts in a week as I’m still suffering from all day nausea. On off days I go for long walks to keep the circulation going.
I’m working through my PT pre/post natal cert and enjoying some new knowledge.
Thank you to all the mommies out there that have been sharing tips & ideas with me 💋💋. Happy training everyone xoxo #babybump #18weekspregnant #positivevibes

Sharing some of my leg day at #20weeks 😝💪🏽... made it to 5 months 🎈... We’re doing TWL DAY 1.. leg day. I only had to make a few modifications. I’m attempting to not lean forward too much.. I changed deadlifts (shown by @kdee_fit ) out for a more upright sumo style deadlift w a kettlebell, and went lighter than usual so I could focus on keeping my abs engaged. I also changed out lying leg (shown by @bbrianadanielle ) with low back ext. w a focus on hamstrings not going too far forward. I’m going to take these out in a week or two, but for now I’m okay with them and I’m making the focus hamstrings. I would otherwise recommend standing ham curl for anyone else. All and all if felt great. I’ll keep listening to my body and only do what feels great!! Excited to do some of the TWL challenge with everyone starting tomorrow. Come join in the fun!! Link in bio 💋💋 #babybump #positivevibes #20weekspregnant

💙💙BABY UPDATE !!!👶🏽 🍼 💙💙Dressing up this baby bump for our family baby shower.
I haven’t checked in for a minute. It’s been a bit crazy prepping for the new @hourglassworkout studio and upcoming baby.
I’m now well into my third trimester and each trimester is definitely quite different. I’m finally not sick daily which is a blessing, lol. My weekly chiropractic pre-hab visits have kept all pains away, woo hoo. I experienced heart-burn for the first time in life.. it sucked. I figured out as long as I don’t have hot chocolate, it won’t come back, phew! I manage to get a workout in about 3 times a week. I’m keeping it light. I do the elliptical for cardio and stick to the basic exercises like squats, non weighted hip thrusts, cable back exercises and dumbbell chest and shoulder exercises. Feeling good, loving my cute bump and this whole experience. Can’t wait to meet our little guy.

Onto #week16.. each week brings something new lol... We haven’t done a lot of sharing but it’s been a pretty interesting experience so far 😊 Weeks 3-6 were easy breezy.. week 6-11 hit me like a ton of bricks!! 😳 all day nausea, fatigue and boobs doubled in size lol 😆 working out was close to impossible but I went twice a week and often threw up at the gym 🤮oops.. food aversions have been interesting... I now dislike cookies, chocolate, meat & veggies 🤨... so what’s left... bread, pickles, olives & fruit🤔... dude... it’s so weird... I force myself to still eat meat & veg as possible, lol. From week 13 - now.. it’s slowly gotten better, back at the gym, and shorter periods of nausea each day.. it’s all so interesting 🤓and of course will all be worth it ❤️.. so... after hearing the symptoms... do you think it’s gonna be a boy or a girl 💖💙😜... #16weekspregnant #boyorgirl #positivevibes

👶🏽👶🏽BABY WORKOUT!! 🍼🍼 #26weekspregnant workout! Leg Day!
So I’m a bit behind in posting this.. life’s been busy 😆... building nursery, baby shower planning and building a new @HourglassWorkout Gym 💕... Woo Hoo 🙌 During this workout, I learned a few things about what exercises feel amazing 👍🏽at the end of 2nd trimester, and which don’t 👎🏽... here’s the list: LOVED: banded hip thrust, shallow cable pull throughs, pilates zip ups, seated machines (ab & ad-ductors, leg extension), no weight step ups on medium step, TRX jump squats with a soft landing and a very low jump), bird dog . TAKING OUT TILL AFTER BIRTH: Bulgarian split squat, back leg elevated dead lift, hamstring curl on the ball, kneeling cable kick backs 😢.. I’ll miss these exercises, but I can feel them causing the same round ligament pain that caused me to walk with a cain for two days... listening & learning and feeling amazing ❤️ PS.. at 6 months I finally went from all day sick to morning sick only .. 🤢.. it’s something and I’ll take it 🙌... thanks so much for sharing this journey with me. Would love to hear what excuses worked & didn’t work for all the mommies out there during pregnancy 🤰 💪🏽... muah 💋 #26weeks #babybump #positivevibes

#23week Baby Workout 🤰❤️🍼
Mixing it up today with a bit of Back & Hamstrings. I’m excited to add some of what I’ve been learning in my pre-post natal certification. I’ve included some kegel breathing between sets in place of where I’d usually do abs. I’m incorporating more squats into my workouts. I’ve taken out all planks, push ups from toes and full deadlifts 😢... still doing light kettlebell deadlifts focusing on my core, but I’ll take those out soon as well most likely. I notice reduced strength in my pull ups.. that was a hit to the ego... but it is what it is, I’ll get it back later 💪🏽. I’ve added additional stretches into my routine. Important ones are: cat/cow, hip flexor stretches, glutes & low back stretches focusing on the SI. 🧘‍♀️ That 6 month mark is creeping up... amazing his quickly thus all goes by. Thanks to everyone sending me tips & love. 🙏🏽 Happy Training everyone 💋❤️ w @getbodiedbyj @kdee_fit #positivevibes #babybump #humpday

#22weeks BABY UPDATE 👶🏽💙🍼
I’ve officially moved from all day sickness to morning sickness. While it’s not common to still be getting nauseous past 5 months... at least it’s getting better 😜
I had a scary trip to emergency 🚨🚨🚨 this week 😱 with sharp stabbing pains in my lower belly causing me to not be able to walk for two days. Turned out to be my round ligaments stretching w the baby. I went to see a pelvic floor physiotherapist. She said my pelvic floor was tight and needed manual release.. ouch! This hurt but helped (Pilates instructor problems). Additionally I saw my chiropractor and my glutes and hip were tight. More manual release ... and bam!! We’re walking again (no more cane 😆)... anyways... this week was full of adventure.. happy to be leaning about what women can go through on this miracle of journey as well as hopefully, his to fix it.
We get more and more excited with each day to meet my little one. Regardless of the obstacles along the way... we feel beyond blessed. The little one is the size of a spaghetti squash this week 👶🏽💙. Thank you to everyone sharing there stories with me. Love y’all ❤️ #22weekspregnant #babybump #positivevibes
The Block is 🔥🔥🔥... #summer2018 #embraceyourcurves #hourglass
